aa(lp273
VSee, Dr. Kean made that shift in thinking.
p274
aVHe understood that there's a difference between the medical condition
p275
aVand what someone might do with it.
p276
aVAnd there's been a shift in my thinking over time,
p277
aVin that, if you had asked me at 15 years old,
p278
aVif I would have traded prosthetics for flesh-and-bone legs,
p279
aVI wouldn't have hesitated for a second.
p280
aVI aspired to that kind of normalcy back then.
p281
aVBut if you ask me today, I'm not so sure.
p282
aVAnd it's because of the experiences I've had with them,
p283
aVnot in spite of the experiences I've had with them.
p284
aVAnd perhaps this shift in me has happened
p285
aVbecause I've been exposed to more people who have opened doors for me
p286
aVthan those who have put lids and cast shadows on me.
