aa(lp321
VSo, I think that the only true disability is a crushed spirit,
p322
aVa spirit that's been crushed doesn't have hope,
p323
aVit doesn't see beauty,
p324
aVit no longer has our natural, childlike curiosity
p325
aVand our innate ability to imagine.
p326
aVIf instead, we can bolster a human spirit to keep hope,
p327
aVto see beauty in themselves and others,
p328
aVto be curious and imaginative,
p329
aVthen we are truly using our power well.
p330
aVWhen a spirit has those qualities, we are able to create new realities
p331
aVand new ways of being.
